postcontent:
For sale is a very nice and hard to find Armalite AR-10(T) Target Model 16" .308/7.62x51 that was a limited run with the 16" barrel vs. the 20" barrel as a 2010 SHOT Show Special.  It features a 16" 1:10 triple lapped stainless steel barrel, slotted aluminum free-float handguard, A2 stock and Armalite's Precision two-stage trigger($1,900 when new).  It comes with MI steel front and rear flip sights($200), seven Armalite brand mags, 5-25rd., 1-20rd. and 1-10rd mag($300), 5" bottom rail section not shown($40) Blackhawk sling and hardcase, so over $2,400 new before any other fees.  Overall, I would say the rifle is in excellent condition with a few very light marks on the left side of the handguard and maybe a couple on the receiver, there are some on the top rail where a scope was mounted.  Weight is about 8 1/2lbs., so if you are looking for the most accurate, compact and lightweight factory AR-10 rifle, here you go!  Here are the specs for the 20" model since the 16" is no longer offered  https://armalite.com/shop/ar-10t-a-series-rifle/ 
$1,900 firm for everything or higher in trade value, no hurry to sell.  I can also take some off if you don't want the MI sights or all the mags, just let me know.I might consider trades if it's a good deal for me, otherwise, I will wait for cash.  If offering a trade, please be specific on exactly what you have and exactly what you are wanting to do so I know the deal.  Also, are you wanting the rifle, all the mags and the sights or?? and are you wanting a straight trade, trade +/- cash or other?? please be specific.  Trades considered would be in this order, semi-auto rifles and pistols, revolvers, then tactical shotguns, lever guns and bolt-guns.
Ammo in the common rifle and pistol calibers to help with a deal, but I have PLENTY already, so...1oz. silver bars, rounds or Eagles and grams of gold.  Maybe optics to help, but I have nice optics sitting now for future projects.Ftf in the Dallas area or will ship insured for $40 more and must be able to legally own a firearm in TX.Thanks for looking!
